21
00:03:21.165 --> 00:03:22.333
<i>But it sure feels like it.</i>

22
00:03:22.416 --> 00:03:24.919
[dramatic music playing]

23
00:03:27.213 --> 00:03:29.381
[grunts]

24
00:03:32.093 --> 00:03:34.345
[breathes heavily]

25
00:03:35.346 --> 00:03:37.765
<i>We're told
to treat our bodies like a temple.</i>

26
00:03:39.308 --> 00:03:40.518
<i>consume nutrients.</i>

27
00:03:40.601 --> 00:03:41.727
<i>burn calories.</i>

28
00:03:43.270 --> 00:03:44.271
<i>fitness.</i>

29
00:03:44.355 --> 00:03:45.731
<i>avoid drive-by's.</i>

30
00:03:49.527 --> 00:03:50.778
<i>We can take a lot.</i>

31
00:03:51.445 --> 00:03:52.446
[grunts]

32
00:03:52.530 --> 00:03:54.740
<i>And that was a lot.</i>

33
00:03:59.829 --> 00:04:01.413
- [rips]
- [spits]

34
00:04:04.416 --> 00:04:05.459
[groaning]

35
00:04:08.003 --> 00:04:09.130
Come on.

36
00:04:11.090 --> 00:04:12.383
[sighs]

37
00:04:27.982 --> 00:04:29.567
[breathes heavily]

38
00:04:45.166 --> 00:04:49.962
[John] <i>Sometimes I close my eyes
and imagine I decided not to stay.</i>

39
00:04:51.046 --> 00:04:54.508
<i>I changed my mind.
I'm flying back with the others.</i>

40
00:04:55.134 --> 00:04:58.888
<i>racing past strange worlds.
unfamiliar stars.</i>

41
00:04:59.764 --> 00:05:04.393
<i>I'm off. I'm free. I'm going home.</i>

42
00:05:05.019 --> 00:05:06.020
[music ends]

43
00:05:07.062 --> 00:05:10.107
<i>- And then I wake up.</i>
- [birds chirping]

44
00:05:10.191 --> 00:05:14.361
<i>I'm still here. so I shower. I shave.</i>

45
00:05:15.321 --> 00:05:18.115
<i>I put on a new suit
and get back to work looking for Ji.</i>

46
00:05:20.576 --> 00:05:21.577
[John] Wow.

47
00:05:21.660 --> 00:05:23.120
[Val] Yeah. he's fast.

48
00:05:24.371 --> 00:05:25.623
So. you all right?

49
00:05:26.791 --> 00:05:28.876
Yeah. I'm fine. it was just. uh...

50
00:05:29.376 --> 00:05:31.545
- Just a lot of blood.
- I thought it was your blood

51
00:05:31.629 --> 00:05:33.214
and you were gonna fucking die
or something.

52
00:05:33.297 --> 00:05:34.340
No. I'm fine. Val.

53
00:05:38.385 --> 00:05:39.553
It's impressive.

54
00:05:39.637 --> 00:05:41.305
Yeah. my guy. he's an artist.

55
00:05:43.599 --> 00:05:44.600
Cool.

56
00:05:45.434 --> 00:05:47.686
All right. how much do I owe you?

57
00:05:49.772 --> 00:05:51.107
We'll figure it out later.

58
00:05:55.319 --> 00:05:56.403
You're good at this.

59
00:05:58.155 --> 00:06:01.367
- I like you. Val.
- I like you too.

60
00:06:01.450 --> 00:06:03.953
Yeah. but things have gotten
more dangerous than I anticipated.

61
00:06:04.036 --> 00:06:05.371
and I don't want you getting hurt.

62
00:06:06.163 --> 00:06:07.289
Yeah. I hear that.

63
00:06:09.708 --> 00:06:12.211
Look. there's a lot of things
that are dangerous out there.

64
00:06:12.294 --> 00:06:14.421
And they don't pay
as well as you do. so. uh...

65
00:06:15.089 --> 00:06:17.049
I get it. I've been warned.

66
00:06:19.343 --> 00:06:20.344
But fuck it.

67
00:06:21.262 --> 00:06:22.847
Besides. I got that camera.

68
00:06:22.930 --> 00:06:24.390
- You did?
- Yeah.

69
00:06:25.141 --> 00:06:26.767
Is it a camera that takes calls?

70
00:06:26.851 --> 00:06:28.811
No. man. it's a camera camera.

71
00:06:28.894 --> 00:06:31.355
- You know how to use it?
- You know.

72
00:06:32.314 --> 00:06:33.315
All right.

73
00:06:38.696 --> 00:06:41.115
[John] <i>LA is the homeless capital
of the world.</i>

74
00:06:41.615 --> 00:06:42.950
<i>Over 40.000 people.</i>

75
00:06:44.160 --> 00:06:48.789
<i>Bad choices. bad outcomes.
but mostly just bad luck.</i>

76
00:06:51.208 --> 00:06:54.837
<i>Human beings can be beautiful.
kind. full of light.</i>

77
00:06:55.838 --> 00:06:58.549
- <i>They can be. I see it every day.</i>
- [dog barking]

78
00:06:58.632 --> 00:07:01.218
<i>And I see how they treat their own
most in pain.</i>

79
00:07:02.011 --> 00:07:05.181
<i>I see it sometimes. and it shocks me.</i>

80
00:07:07.808 --> 00:07:10.561
[people shouting indistinctly]

81
00:07:19.487 --> 00:07:20.821
Sandra Jaquez?

82
00:07:21.655 --> 00:07:22.656
Yes?

83
00:07:23.282 --> 00:07:26.702
Hi. Um. my name is John Sugar.

84
00:07:29.079 --> 00:07:30.080
Hello.

85
00:07:30.164 --> 00:07:31.165
Hello.

86
00:07:33.584 --> 00:07:37.254
Your son. Jesus... Chuy.

87
00:07:38.130 --> 00:07:41.509
I wanted to ask. you heard what happened?

88
00:07:46.222 --> 00:07:47.431
I heard.

89
00:07:48.849 --> 00:07:49.850
I'm sorry.

90
00:07:53.145 --> 00:07:55.022
Thanks. [sniffles]

91
00:07:55.106 --> 00:07:57.024
I can. uh... I can come back another time.

92
00:07:57.900 --> 00:07:59.443
No. now. uh...

93
00:08:01.112 --> 00:08:02.530
But not here.

94
00:08:03.447 --> 00:08:04.740
[John] I'm so sorry.

95
00:08:05.449 --> 00:08:07.159
Chuy was always a good boy.

96
00:08:07.701 --> 00:08:09.161
Always had a conscience.

97
00:08:10.079 --> 00:08:12.331
Even when he was out with those others.
doing what they do.

98
00:08:12.414 --> 00:08:13.624
You mean the Ez4s?

99
00:08:14.250 --> 00:08:17.461
Bad boys. Not funny. not like the movie.

100
00:08:18.170 --> 00:08:21.549
Can you think of any reason why someone
might have wanted to hurt your son?

101
00:08:22.550 --> 00:08:26.554
[scoffs] I don't have to think of a reason
for someone to hurt my son. I know it.

102
00:08:28.472 --> 00:08:30.099
It's all because of Fire Sale.

103
00:08:30.808 --> 00:08:32.017
Fire Sale?

104
00:08:32.101 --> 00:08:33.394
Feeding us the Fentanyl.

105
00:08:33.476 --> 00:08:34.644
Chuy didn't like it.

106
00:08:34.728 --> 00:08:36.689
I-I told him you better keep quiet.

107
00:08:37.440 --> 00:08:40.359
They'll-They'll get you like they got Kobe
and Johnnie Cochran.

108
00:08:40.442 --> 00:08:43.654
But Chuy didn't listen.
And those bad friends of his.

109
00:08:43.737 --> 00:08:46.157
So. they got him. He's gone.

110
00:08:48.742 --> 00:08:51.787
Careful. or they'll get you too.

111
00:08:53.664 --> 00:08:54.999
Hey. Sandra.

112
00:08:55.666 --> 00:08:56.876
You take care.

113
00:08:58.586 --> 00:09:01.464
[speaking Spanish]

114
00:09:04.216 --> 00:09:06.635
[sorrowful music playing]

115
00:09:21.484 --> 00:09:22.485
- Hey.
- Hey.

116
00:09:22.568 --> 00:09:24.779
[John] <i>Dave and Bunny.
from the other night.</i>

117
00:09:25.362 --> 00:09:26.822
<i>Their friend had just OD'd.</i>

118
00:09:26.906 --> 00:09:28.574
Still looking for that kid?

119
00:09:28.657 --> 00:09:30.826
Yeah. yeah. Uh. where are you headed?

120
00:09:31.368 --> 00:09:32.661
[Bunny] We got an apartment.

121
00:09:32.745 --> 00:09:34.622
You got an apartment? That's amazing.

122
00:09:34.705 --> 00:09:39.001
It's a new program.
We passed a piss test. so we qualified.

123
00:09:39.084 --> 00:09:41.545
We'll call you.
We'll have you over once we're settled.

124
00:09:41.629 --> 00:09:44.006
- It's a deal. You still got my card?
- [Bunny] Yep.

125
00:09:44.090 --> 00:09:46.258
Congratulations. It's amazing.

126
00:09:54.141 --> 00:09:55.226
["Great Wall of America" playing]

127
00:09:55.309 --> 00:09:56.310
[grunts]

128
00:09:59.021 --> 00:10:00.606
[grunting]

129
00:10:05.111 --> 00:10:06.112
[bell rings]

130
00:10:09.782 --> 00:10:10.866
[Teddy] Hold up. kid.

131
00:10:13.702 --> 00:10:15.246
Someone I want you to meet.

132
00:10:15.955 --> 00:10:18.916
Len Pankow. Mind if we... we interrupt?

133
00:10:19.959 --> 00:10:20.960
No.

134
00:10:21.043 --> 00:10:22.962
Saw you fight Mbanefo the other night.

135
00:10:23.462 --> 00:10:25.798
What he outweigh you? Twenty-five pounds?

136
00:10:25.881 --> 00:10:26.882
Twenty-eight pounds.

137
00:10:26.966 --> 00:10:28.342
Geez. [chuckles]

138
00:10:28.426 --> 00:10:32.430
Nice job. Nice job.
Good feet. you stick and you slip well.

139
00:10:32.930 --> 00:10:34.223
Thanks.

140
00:10:34.306 --> 00:10:35.558
You know Nestor Rodrigues?

141
00:10:35.641 --> 00:10:38.102
Of course he does.
Who doesn't know Nestor?

142
00:10:38.185 --> 00:10:39.311
I know him.

143
00:10:39.395 --> 00:10:42.523
Wanna talk about coming to Vegas.
fighting him for me?

144
00:10:44.775 --> 00:10:45.776
For real?

145
00:10:45.860 --> 00:10:48.028
Yeah. we can break bread.
we can talk about it.

146
00:10:48.112 --> 00:10:49.447
You like sushi?

147
00:10:50.030 --> 00:10:51.031
Sure.

148
00:10:52.867 --> 00:10:54.118
All right. champ.

149
00:10:55.077 --> 00:10:56.162
All right. Next time.

150
00:10:56.662 --> 00:10:57.663
Thank you.

151
00:10:57.746 --> 00:11:00.374
[music continues]

152
00:11:03.002 --> 00:11:06.547
Jesus. kid.
Nestor fucking Rodrigues in Vegas.

153
00:11:07.256 --> 00:11:09.091
Would it kill you to fucking smile?

154
00:11:09.175 --> 00:11:10.176
[chuckles]

155
00:11:11.010 --> 00:11:14.013
- [Teddy] Congratulations. You earned it.
- Thanks. man. Thanks. Teddy.

156
00:11:15.055 --> 00:11:16.056
[chuckles]

157
00:11:16.140 --> 00:11:17.349
[music ends]

158
00:11:25.691 --> 00:11:28.235
[phone ringing]

159
00:11:29.653 --> 00:11:30.654
[club music through phone]

160
00:11:30.738 --> 00:11:31.906
- Ji?
- [Ji] <i>Moon bro!</i>

161
00:11:31.989 --> 00:11:33.991
- What the fuck?
<i>- Are you there? Can you hear me?</i>

162
00:11:34.074 --> 00:11:36.577
I can hear you. What the f...
What's going on? Where are you?

163
00:11:36.660 --> 00:11:39.413
<i>I got your message.
I know you're mad. but it's gonna be okay.</i>

164
00:11:39.497 --> 00:11:41.791
There are people looking for you.
Where are you?

165
00:11:41.874 --> 00:11:42.875
[club music continues]

166
00:11:42.958 --> 00:11:44.418
[Val] Home.

167
00:11:45.795 --> 00:11:47.046
Manual mode.

168
00:11:47.129 --> 00:11:48.714
Shutter speed.

169
00:11:50.091 --> 00:11:51.383
Shutter priority.

170
00:11:51.467 --> 00:11:54.929
Like I said. just use auto mode at first.
It's... That's easiest.

171
00:11:55.012 --> 00:11:56.013
All right.

172
00:11:57.389 --> 00:11:58.390
How are those?

173
00:11:59.767 --> 00:12:00.935
They're good.

174
00:12:03.604 --> 00:12:05.272
- I think I got it. Yeah.
- Yeah?

175
00:12:05.356 --> 00:12:08.275
All right. Watch Hannah's house.
If Ji shows up. let me know. That's it.

176
00:12:08.359 --> 00:12:10.569
- [Val] Pretty cool.
- [phone ringing]

177
00:12:12.780 --> 00:12:13.948
Danny. hey. What's up?

178
00:12:14.031 --> 00:12:15.866
[Danny] <i>Yo. Ji just called me.</i>

179
00:12:16.450 --> 00:12:20.079
<i>And. uh... And these guys.
they're following me. man.</i>

180
00:12:20.830 --> 00:12:22.665
- [door closes]
- Where are you now?

181
00:12:29.797 --> 00:12:30.798
Can I help you. sir?

182
00:12:30.881 --> 00:12:32.508
[in Spanish] I know you guys
are busy right now.

183
00:12:32.591 --> 00:12:34.552
but when you have a moment

184
00:12:34.635 --> 00:12:36.512
tell your boss.

185
00:12:36.595 --> 00:12:38.431
I haven't forgotten

186
00:12:39.348 --> 00:12:41.434
and that I'll be talking to him soon.

187
00:12:42.852 --> 00:12:44.520
Pass that along for me?

188
00:12:45.896 --> 00:12:46.897
Thank you.

189
00:12:49.066 --> 00:12:51.527
[John. in English] <i>Ez soldiers
keeping an eye on Danny.</i>

190
00:12:51.610 --> 00:12:53.446
<i>hoping he leads them to his brother.</i>

191
00:12:55.156 --> 00:12:59.785
<i>I'm glad Danny called.
Still doesn't trust me. but it's progress.</i>

192
00:12:59.869 --> 00:13:00.870
[Danny] That's it?

193
00:13:01.495 --> 00:13:02.496
What do you mean?

194
00:13:02.580 --> 00:13:05.249
[stammers] I thought you were gonna
show 'em your gun or something.

195
00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:07.418
I don't carry a gun.

196
00:13:07.501 --> 00:13:10.004
Uh. the club that Ji called from.
do you know where it is?

197
00:13:10.087 --> 00:13:12.506
I'll show you.
but how are we gonna lose them?

198
00:13:13.257 --> 00:13:14.258
By driving away.

199
00:13:16.552 --> 00:13:19.305
[tires screech]

200
00:13:19.388 --> 00:13:22.099
["Going Out Tonight" playing]

201
00:13:22.183 --> 00:13:24.477
- [brakes screech]
- [horn honks]

202
00:13:29.774 --> 00:13:31.859
[music continues]

203
00:14:01.764 --> 00:14:03.224
[John] <i>There's music on our planet.</i>

204
00:14:04.433 --> 00:14:08.062
<i>A single note sustained
through a stalk of folded grass.</i>

205
00:14:08.145 --> 00:14:09.855
[piano music playing]

206
00:14:09.939 --> 00:14:12.608
<i>But the music here is...</i>

207
00:14:14.276 --> 00:14:16.904
<i>Well. it's different.</i>

208
00:14:53.190 --> 00:14:54.400
[piano music ends]

209
00:14:54.483 --> 00:14:56.068
["Bang" playing]

210
00:15:00.489 --> 00:15:01.490
Peg?

211
00:15:05.786 --> 00:15:06.787
Peg!

212
00:15:09.039 --> 00:15:13.711
Sugar! Look at you!
Out on the dance floor.

213
00:15:14.712 --> 00:15:15.838
[dancer] My bad.

214
00:15:17.965 --> 00:15:18.966
Hey!

215
00:15:20.885 --> 00:15:22.511
[stammers] Sorry.

216
00:15:23.137 --> 00:15:24.138
You're okay.

217
00:15:29.518 --> 00:15:30.603
Ji-Ho!

218
00:15:32.521 --> 00:15:33.898
What the hell are you doing?

219
00:15:35.149 --> 00:15:36.150
I know.

220
00:15:36.233 --> 00:15:39.278
[in Korean] Tina and I
were just hitting the...

221
00:15:40.404 --> 00:15:41.572
Tina?

222
00:15:42.156 --> 00:15:43.574
Oh shit...

223
00:15:43.657 --> 00:15:45.034
Noelle... sorry.

224
00:15:46.702 --> 00:15:48.370
[Ji chuckles]

225
00:15:49.705 --> 00:15:50.748
[speaks indistinctly]

226
00:15:51.874 --> 00:15:54.919
- [in English] What's with the hair?
- [sniffs] It's sick. right?

227
00:15:55.503 --> 00:15:56.587
Undercover.

228
00:15:57.755 --> 00:16:00.216
Got this fucking guy after me.

229
00:16:00.299 --> 00:16:02.051
This fucking guy...

230
00:16:02.134 --> 00:16:04.762
- What guy?
- [mutters] You have no idea.

231
00:16:04.845 --> 00:16:06.138
What are you talking about?

232
00:16:06.222 --> 00:16:08.516
We just... We gotta be careful.

233
00:16:08.599 --> 00:16:11.852
Fucked up and high in a nightclub
is fucking careful to you?

234
00:16:11.936 --> 00:16:14.146
[sighs] It's fine. man. Fuck! Okay.

235
00:16:15.231 --> 00:16:20.236
We set this thing up. we go to the desert.
chill. let that shit die down.

236
00:16:20.319 --> 00:16:23.197
and then boom. we're back. baby.
Moon Bros!

237
00:16:23.280 --> 00:16:26.200
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- Bro. we got some money coming in.

238
00:16:26.283 --> 00:16:29.495
The money from the drugs that you stole
from a fucking hospital?

239
00:16:32.581 --> 00:16:34.375
You think you're better than me?

240
00:16:34.458 --> 00:16:35.543
I didn't say that.

241
00:16:35.626 --> 00:16:37.670
- You're not better than me.
- Fucking A. man.

242
00:16:38.671 --> 00:16:40.089
I'm just glad we found you. man.

243
00:16:41.173 --> 00:16:42.508
We who? Who's we?

244
00:16:45.219 --> 00:16:46.512
Who the fuck is that?

245
00:16:46.595 --> 00:16:49.348
- That's Sugar. He's been help...
- What the fuck? I said no cops.

246
00:16:50.808 --> 00:16:52.560
[crowd screams]

247
00:16:56.564 --> 00:16:57.565
Hey!

248
00:16:57.648 --> 00:16:58.941
Get the fuck out of here!

249
00:17:03.696 --> 00:17:04.989
Ji!

250
00:17:07.031 --> 00:17:08.116
[grunts]

251
00:17:08.200 --> 00:17:09.285
Sorry. man.

252
00:17:10.202 --> 00:17:13.038
[panting] Come on! Let's go!

253
00:17:13.622 --> 00:17:14.623
Ji!

254
00:17:16.291 --> 00:17:17.793
I said no cops!

255
00:17:18.544 --> 00:17:19.545
Fuck!

256
00:17:19.627 --> 00:17:23.674
- [groaning]
- Sugar. are you okay?

257
00:17:35.102 --> 00:17:37.563
- Here you go.
- Oh. Thanks.

258
00:17:40.649 --> 00:17:41.650
Ji did that.

259
00:17:41.734 --> 00:17:42.735
Yeah?

260
00:17:44.028 --> 00:17:47.490
Wow. it's-it's beautiful. Is it your mom?

261
00:17:48.949 --> 00:17:50.534
Yeah. just before she died.

262
00:17:52.912 --> 00:17:55.498
She was diagnosed six months
after we came here.

263
00:17:55.581 --> 00:17:57.041
And died six months after that.

264
00:17:59.835 --> 00:18:01.837
Ji was 16. and I was ten.

265
00:18:02.922 --> 00:18:04.757
Welcome to America. right?

266
00:18:05.966 --> 00:18:07.384
Wow. you were just kids.

267
00:18:13.140 --> 00:18:14.350
What about your dad?

268
00:18:16.811 --> 00:18:19.772
My dad stayed in Korea.

269
00:18:22.358 --> 00:18:24.568
He's why Mom took us away
in the first place.

270
00:18:25.694 --> 00:18:26.904
It's just us.

271
00:18:28.030 --> 00:18:30.991
For a while now. it's just...
just me and Ji.

272
00:18:31.075 --> 00:18:35.079
[John] <i>Strangers in a strange land.
I know the feeling.</i>

273
00:18:36.163 --> 00:18:40.417
[chuckles] He may even live long enough
to see his big drug deal.

274
00:18:42.461 --> 00:18:44.713
The guy he was with in the club.
do you recognize him?

275
00:18:47.341 --> 00:18:48.342
No.

276
00:18:58.310 --> 00:18:59.437
Don't give up on him.

277
00:18:59.520 --> 00:19:01.981
I don't know. Sugar.
I think he's given up on himself.

278
00:19:02.731 --> 00:19:05.317
[somber music playing]

279
00:19:12.408 --> 00:19:13.701
Uh...

280
00:19:13.784 --> 00:19:18.205
[sighs] Fourteen suits. by the way.

281
00:19:20.207 --> 00:19:21.459
Damn. [chuckles]

282
00:19:21.542 --> 00:19:23.002
You went back and counted?

283
00:19:23.085 --> 00:19:25.421
Yeah. of course.
I mean. you made me think.

284
00:19:26.839 --> 00:19:28.048
[chuckles]

285
00:19:29.091 --> 00:19:30.968
Fourteen suits.

286
00:19:31.051 --> 00:19:32.720
Not including the ones I got in storage.

287
00:19:34.472 --> 00:19:37.016
Huh. Baller.

288
00:19:37.600 --> 00:19:39.310
[laughing]

289
00:19:41.812 --> 00:19:42.980
I'm sorry about your...

290
00:19:43.814 --> 00:19:45.232
Ah. it's okay.

291
00:19:48.652 --> 00:19:51.697
[John] <i>Siblings are complicated.
Everyone knows that.</i>

292
00:19:54.366 --> 00:19:56.118
<i>Doesn't matter where you're from.</i>

293
00:19:59.079 --> 00:20:02.750
<i>My sister and I.
we drove each other crazy sometimes.</i>

294
00:20:03.709 --> 00:20:05.503
<i>But I'd do anything to get her back.</i>

295
00:20:08.005 --> 00:20:09.840
<i>That's why this case matters to me.</i>

296
00:20:10.549 --> 00:20:12.384
<i>why they all do. I suppose.</i>

297
00:20:25.022 --> 00:20:26.232
[John] <i>"Fire Sale."</i>

298
00:20:26.315 --> 00:20:28.984
<i>That's what Sandra Jaquez said
got Chuy killed.</i>

299
00:20:34.615 --> 00:20:36.617
[actor 1 on TV] <i>I'll tell you why.
Because you warned him.</i>

300
00:20:36.700 --> 00:20:38.869
<i>That's why he came early.
That's why he came in the back way.</i>

301
00:20:38.953 --> 00:20:41.247
[actor 2] <i>But you heard me tell him
the front door would be open.</i>

302
00:20:41.330 --> 00:20:43.707
<i>- And the key to let him in the back way?
- He must have had one made.</i>

303
00:20:43.791 --> 00:20:45.167
<i>- Why don't you tell us the truth?
- Marty.</i>

304
00:20:55.052 --> 00:20:57.179
[TV continues. indistinct]

305
00:20:57.263 --> 00:20:58.597
[phone buzzes]

306
00:21:04.186 --> 00:21:05.187
Hey.

307
00:21:06.230 --> 00:21:08.149
[Val] <i>This is actually pretty boring.</i>

308
00:21:08.232 --> 00:21:10.943
I know. [chuckling] No sign of Ji?

309
00:21:11.569 --> 00:21:12.570
Nope.

310
00:21:13.487 --> 00:21:14.488
<i>You're all right?</i>

311
00:21:15.489 --> 00:21:17.741
If he's on the run.
then why would he show up here?

312
00:21:19.743 --> 00:21:21.036
Uh. maybe he won't.

313
00:21:21.120 --> 00:21:23.831
But he's on the run
with a lot of drugs to unload.

314
00:21:23.914 --> 00:21:26.917
so maybe he'll need help with that part.
What else?

315
00:21:30.004 --> 00:21:31.589
What do I do if I need to pee?

316
00:21:31.672 --> 00:21:33.716
Well. if you gotta go. you gotta go. Val.

317
00:21:34.258 --> 00:21:35.593
<i>Right. no. yeah. I just...</i>

318
00:21:36.385 --> 00:21:37.511
I don't know. I thought...

319
00:21:37.595 --> 00:21:40.055
Maybe there were some specific rules
that I need to follow.

320
00:21:41.348 --> 00:21:42.433
Good night. Val.

321
00:21:42.516 --> 00:21:43.601
Good night. Sugar.

322
00:21:43.684 --> 00:21:46.270
[on TV] <i>Maybe Martin will
come back for it. then we can ask him.</i>

323
00:21:48.439 --> 00:21:51.484
<i>Here. Nevertheless.
I want a 24-hour tail put on Reeves...</i>

324
00:21:51.567 --> 00:21:52.651
[John sighs]

325
00:21:52.735 --> 00:21:54.695
<i>...and I want a watch
on his home and his factory.</i>

326
00:21:54.779 --> 00:21:56.280
[piano music playing]

327
00:21:58.783 --> 00:22:00.868
[sighing]

328
00:22:00.951 --> 00:22:02.453
[water crashes]

329
00:22:06.415 --> 00:22:10.002
[John] <i>I wanted a case to keep me busy.
and this one's doing the trick so far.</i>

330
00:22:10.544 --> 00:22:11.879
<i>That's the good news.</i>

331
00:22:12.797 --> 00:22:15.007
<i>Still. that woman at the club.</i>

332
00:22:16.675 --> 00:22:18.928
<i>I just hope I'm not seeing ghosts again.</i>

333
00:22:26.185 --> 00:22:27.353
[exhales]

334
00:22:32.983 --> 00:22:35.653
Are you stalking me or am I stalking you?

335
00:22:35.736 --> 00:22:38.239
Uh... [chuckles] Neither. I hope.

336
00:22:39.490 --> 00:22:40.991
Or both would be better.

337
00:22:50.876 --> 00:22:52.628
- Hey.
- Hey.

338
00:22:53.254 --> 00:22:54.922
Can I talk to you about something?

339
00:22:55.506 --> 00:22:56.507
Sure.

340
00:22:59.093 --> 00:23:01.095
One nice person to another?

341
00:23:01.679 --> 00:23:03.764
[chuckles] Yeah. that's us.

342
00:23:04.640 --> 00:23:09.186
Ethical question. Work question.
I'm curious your opinion. You ready?

343
00:23:09.270 --> 00:23:10.271
Go ahead.

344
00:23:10.354 --> 00:23:11.564
I love my job.

345
00:23:12.231 --> 00:23:13.983
Good people trying to do good things

346
00:23:14.066 --> 00:23:16.068
to make the world a better place
for the most part.

347
00:23:16.152 --> 00:23:17.653
You're passionate humanitarians.

348
00:23:17.736 --> 00:23:19.989
And for me. it's true.
I believe in what I do.

349
00:23:20.072 --> 00:23:21.073
[John exhales sharply]

350
00:23:21.157 --> 00:23:26.078
But do certain ends justify any means
is the question.

351
00:23:26.662 --> 00:23:29.331
Uh. sounds like a slippery slope so far.

352
00:23:29.415 --> 00:23:32.460
I mean. any means?

353
00:23:32.543 --> 00:23:36.088
[chuckling] No. no.
It's nothing scary or illegal.

354
00:23:36.172 --> 00:23:38.090
- [chuckles]
- We're not... It's nothing like that.

355
00:23:38.174 --> 00:23:41.719
They just had us sign this NDA out of.
like. George Orwell.

356
00:23:41.802 --> 00:23:46.766
otherwise I'd be less whatever it is
that I am currently being. [chuckles]

357
00:23:46.849 --> 00:23:48.058
Mysterious?

358
00:23:49.393 --> 00:23:52.855
Uh. obscure? Cryptic?

359
00:23:53.856 --> 00:23:56.400
I was gonna say annoying. but fine.

360
00:23:56.901 --> 00:23:59.069
But I hear you on the slippery slope part.

361
00:24:00.446 --> 00:24:03.616
It's always something to watch out for
in the world of good intentions.

362
00:24:03.699 --> 00:24:04.700
so thank you.

363
00:24:06.202 --> 00:24:08.537
That's it? That's what...
You swam over. and you're...

364
00:24:09.413 --> 00:24:11.332
You're satisfied with slippery slope?

365
00:24:11.874 --> 00:24:13.918
I am completely satisfied.

366
00:24:17.463 --> 00:24:18.798
You're a hard person to read.

367
00:24:18.881 --> 00:24:21.050
[chuckles] Yeah. I've heard that.

368
00:24:21.634 --> 00:24:23.344
That's another thing they say
about you. huh?

369
00:24:23.427 --> 00:24:24.553
Mmm. All the time.

370
00:24:24.637 --> 00:24:27.348
Only. I don't get it.
I think I'm pretty open-and-shut.

371
00:24:29.058 --> 00:24:33.145
I mean. you can read me now. right?

372
00:24:39.110 --> 00:24:40.111
Yes...

373
00:24:45.199 --> 00:24:47.118
["Dear Mr. Dee Jay" playing]

374
00:24:47.201 --> 00:24:48.244
...and no.

375
00:24:49.286 --> 00:24:50.913
Yes and no?

376
00:24:52.706 --> 00:24:54.583
You're not so easy to read yourself.

377
00:25:10.433 --> 00:25:11.434
[lock clicks]

378
00:25:15.020 --> 00:25:16.313
[door closes]

379
00:25:18.357 --> 00:25:19.567
[sighs]

380
00:25:22.194 --> 00:25:23.487
[sighs]

381
00:25:23.571 --> 00:25:25.823
[John] <i>There are rules one has to follow.</i>

382
00:25:25.906 --> 00:25:26.907
<i>Guidelines.</i>

383
00:25:27.867 --> 00:25:29.785
<i>Things we're warned not to do.</i>

384
00:25:29.869 --> 00:25:31.579
<i>We are not them. we're told.</i>

385
00:25:31.662 --> 00:25:33.747
[alarm rings]

386
00:25:33.831 --> 00:25:37.001
- [water running. turns off]
<i>- But still. that was fun.</i>

387
00:25:37.084 --> 00:25:38.502
[phone buzzes]

388
00:25:44.133 --> 00:25:45.134
Hey.

389
00:25:45.217 --> 00:25:47.136
[Tom] <i>Morning. I got some news for you.</i>

390
00:25:47.219 --> 00:25:51.223
I heard from my guy in the Anti-Gang Unit
about these Ez4s.

391
00:25:51.307 --> 00:25:54.685
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah. Sex. drugs and rock 'n' roll.

392
00:25:54.769 --> 00:25:56.145
They're a heavy fucking crew.

393
00:25:56.937 --> 00:25:57.938
All right.

394
00:25:59.106 --> 00:26:00.107
Territories?

395
00:26:00.191 --> 00:26:02.485
Roughly between Union and the park.

396
00:26:02.568 --> 00:26:03.569
Downer Town.

397
00:26:03.652 --> 00:26:05.821
Which by and large
makes them a Mexican gang.

398
00:26:05.905 --> 00:26:09.200
But your missing kid is Korean
who made their list because?

399
00:26:10.326 --> 00:26:12.661
Because of reasons
as yet to be determined.

400
00:26:12.745 --> 00:26:13.829
Roger that.

401
00:26:13.913 --> 00:26:16.248
Help me drill down on these Ez4s.

402
00:26:17.374 --> 00:26:21.212
I mean. if I want a better understanding
of their reasoning.

403
00:26:21.295 --> 00:26:23.130
I go to Downer Town. who do I talk to?

404
00:26:23.214 --> 00:26:25.007
- Fuck. man.
- What?

405
00:26:25.091 --> 00:26:27.676
You're a long way from Beverly Hills
with this crew.

406
00:26:27.760 --> 00:26:29.804
I'll drive. I got a car. Who do I talk to?

407
00:26:29.887 --> 00:26:34.517
Head of the gang is a guy
by the name of Jose Alejandro Cortez.

408
00:26:34.600 --> 00:26:38.979
- Mm-hmm.
- But everybody calls him "Jose Guapo."

409
00:26:39.605 --> 00:26:40.940
And he ain't your typical banger.

410
00:26:41.023 --> 00:26:44.443
He's a killer. he got a sheet. all that.
but he's disciplined. he's smart.

411
00:26:44.527 --> 00:26:49.532
And. on top of all that.
he moves product for the Universales.

412
00:26:51.033 --> 00:26:52.868
Your old friend. Sergey.

413
00:26:52.952 --> 00:26:54.537
Sergey was many things.

414
00:26:54.620 --> 00:26:57.248
and we were friendly for a moment in time.
but he ain't no friend of mine.

415
00:26:57.331 --> 00:26:58.707
- No. he is not.
- Uh-uh.

416
00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:01.669
So to sum up...

417
00:27:01.752 --> 00:27:04.964
wherever your on-the-run kid is.
he better keep fuckin' runnin'.

418
00:27:05.047 --> 00:27:06.799
[coughing]

419
00:27:06.882 --> 00:27:08.008
I'm fine.

420
00:27:08.092 --> 00:27:09.343
You quit. right?

421
00:27:09.427 --> 00:27:10.928
Yeah. pretty much. [coughs]

422
00:27:14.849 --> 00:27:16.225
Yeah. here we go.

423
00:27:16.851 --> 00:27:19.395
Another one
of your fuckin' Chinatowns. man.

424
00:27:21.439 --> 00:27:22.565
- All right.
- Yep.

425
00:27:23.107 --> 00:27:24.108
Thanks. Tom.

426
00:27:26.277 --> 00:27:27.570
Hey. what about your dog?

427
00:27:28.946 --> 00:27:30.156
Ah. he's gone.

428
00:27:30.698 --> 00:27:33.451
Yeah. I just like comin' here.

429
00:28:08.444 --> 00:28:09.570
[John] We meet again.

430
00:28:10.571 --> 00:28:11.572
Uh-huh.

431
00:28:14.408 --> 00:28:16.577
How's that pension plan coming along?

432
00:28:16.660 --> 00:28:19.079
Stackin'. Putting it in crypto.

433
00:28:20.372 --> 00:28:22.583
- I know who I'm looking for now.
- Oh. yeah?

434
00:28:22.666 --> 00:28:23.667
Yeah.

435
00:28:25.044 --> 00:28:26.045
Guapo.

436
00:28:27.087 --> 00:28:28.297
You know him?

437
00:28:28.380 --> 00:28:32.009
[chuckles] Do I know Guapo?

438
00:28:32.676 --> 00:28:34.345
He's <i>el jefe</i> around here.

439
00:28:34.428 --> 00:28:35.429
Good.

440
00:28:36.764 --> 00:28:38.390
He's who I wanna talk to.

441
00:28:38.474 --> 00:28:41.102
Passed it along. No one got back to you?

442
00:28:41.185 --> 00:28:44.480
[chuckles] Yeah. they did.
They. uh... They tried to kill me.

443
00:28:45.523 --> 00:28:48.067
- Oh. word? That's cold.
- Uh-huh.

444
00:28:48.651 --> 00:28:50.152
It is what it is.

445
00:28:51.028 --> 00:28:54.073
And so what? Back for more?

446
00:28:54.156 --> 00:28:57.827
Uh. I'm back because I...
Yeah. I believe there's a way for us...

447
00:28:57.910 --> 00:29:02.456
for. uh. Guapo and I to clear this up
without anyone else getting hurt.

448
00:29:02.540 --> 00:29:04.083
Nonviolence.

449
00:29:05.751 --> 00:29:08.254
Nice. Righteous.

450
00:29:11.674 --> 00:29:15.845
Or. I mean. I could just ask him
about the Fire Sale in Downer Town.

451
00:29:20.850 --> 00:29:24.562
Oh. man.
That's some open sesame shit right there.

452
00:29:24.645 --> 00:29:25.688
It is what it is.

453
00:29:27.231 --> 00:29:28.232
All right.

454
00:29:29.817 --> 00:29:32.111
- Take you to him. Come on.
- Good.

455
00:29:32.194 --> 00:29:33.779
["I Must Be High" playing]

456
00:30:09.064 --> 00:30:11.066
[Spanish rap music playing on loudspeaker]

457
00:30:19.450 --> 00:30:21.076
[volume increases]

458
00:30:51.398 --> 00:30:52.650
You're Guapo?

459
00:30:53.609 --> 00:30:54.610
[chuckles]

460
00:30:56.237 --> 00:30:57.238
You. uh...

461
00:30:58.656 --> 00:31:00.366
You dropped this.

462
00:31:04.662 --> 00:31:07.164
[sighs] Who told you about Fire Sale?

463
00:31:07.832 --> 00:31:09.667
Saw it written on a wall somewhere.

464
00:31:10.292 --> 00:31:13.295
[chuckles] You're hard. That's cool.

465
00:31:14.004 --> 00:31:17.216
That's what I heard.
but won't get you outta this room.

466
00:31:19.343 --> 00:31:20.428
[Guapo sighs]

467
00:31:22.388 --> 00:31:23.389
[hammer cocks]

468
00:31:23.472 --> 00:31:26.684
So's you know. all this?

469
00:31:27.351 --> 00:31:32.648
Chuy Jaquez. Fire Sale. Not my idea.

470
00:31:34.567 --> 00:31:36.360
Whose idea was it?

471
00:31:36.444 --> 00:31:38.446
- [police sirens wailing]
- [shouting in Spanish]

472
00:31:39.113 --> 00:31:40.614
- [gunfire]
- [people screaming]

473
00:31:40.698 --> 00:31:42.783
- What the fuck?
- [officer] Move. move. move.

474
00:31:42.867 --> 00:31:44.785
[pounds on door]

475
00:31:44.869 --> 00:31:47.830
- [gunfire continues]
- [police shouting]

476
00:31:47.913 --> 00:31:48.956
How did you find me?

477
00:31:50.124 --> 00:31:52.835
[grunting. breathing heavily]

478
00:31:58.340 --> 00:32:00.259
Sheriff's Department! Show us your hands!

479
00:32:06.098 --> 00:32:08.309
[somber music plays]

480
00:32:10.186 --> 00:32:12.563
[police radio chatter]

481
00:32:43.552 --> 00:32:45.471
[police radio chatter]

482
00:33:03.948 --> 00:33:05.533
I got him. Cut him loose.

483
00:33:06.325 --> 00:33:07.576
Thank you.

484
00:33:07.660 --> 00:33:08.661
Come with me.

485
00:33:08.744 --> 00:33:10.329
[helicopter whirring]

486
00:33:14.333 --> 00:33:16.836
- Hey. You all right?
- [John] Yeah. I'm all right.

487
00:33:16.919 --> 00:33:17.920
Lucky man.

488
00:33:19.505 --> 00:33:21.215
What are you doing in this neighborhood?

489
00:33:21.298 --> 00:33:23.759
Uh. private investigator
looking for a missing kid.

490
00:33:23.843 --> 00:33:25.344
- Have some ID?
- Yeah. sure.

491
00:33:26.345 --> 00:33:27.346
[John sighs]

492
00:33:28.431 --> 00:33:30.224
Driver's license and P.I. license.

493
00:33:34.186 --> 00:33:35.229
[officer] John Sugar.

494
00:33:37.731 --> 00:33:40.192
[ominous music plays]

495
00:34:02.339 --> 00:34:05.968
["Buggin' Out" playing]

495
00:34:06.305 --> 00:35:06.258
